<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/21(Sun. online meeting) 10 Friends Everyone Should AVOID &amp; How to speak so that people want to listen (Host:Shuman)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=561&amp;p=584#p584"><![CDATA[
11/21(Sun.) 10 Friends Everyone Should AVOID &amp; How to speak so that people want to listen (Host:Shuman)<br /><br />This is online meeting.<br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />At the presentation, the time limit is 1-2 minutes for each speaker.<br /><br />10 Friends Everyone Should AVOID!<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fStuMPuxa5k">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fStuMPuxa5k</a><!-- m --><br />1. The negative friend<br />2. The competitive friend<br />3. The friends with benefits<br />4. The justified friend<br />5. Friend always wants to fight<br />6. The P.A.U friend(acronym friend)<br />7. Clueless friend<br />8. Social friend<br />9. Donald Trump<br />10. Always like to interrupt you<br /><br />Question<br />1. What kind of friend you get rid of?<br />2. What kind of friend you keep it?<br />3. Have some friends had hurt you? Tell us your story.<br />4. How do you know the friend is worth to making when we meet only few times?<br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Article 2 : How to speak so that people want to listen (如何讓別人聽你說話)<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/14453?ref=ted">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/14453?ref=ted</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussions:<br />Q1. Have you made any bad habit of speaking mentioned earlier in this article? Does it bring any consequence or loss to you?<br />Q2. Do you think “HAIL” which the speaker mentions here can really help improve your conversation skills?<br />Q3. Do you exercise your voice skills to make your conversation more popular? Please share your experience.<br />Q4. How should you speak so that people want to listen to you much more after reading this article?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Sun Nov 14, 2021 10:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
